## Segmentation Task

1. Affinity-map subjects by behavioral axes:
   - JTBD pattern (not job title)
   - Adoption-trajectory shape (what drove them to try, what determined outcome)
   - Constraint profile (what limits their choices)
   - Failure/abandonment mode (what causes them to leave or reject)

2. Cluster into 3-5 behavioral segments. Each segment must:
   - Have a behavioral name (not "Enterprise Users" or "SMBs")
   - Contain ≥2 subjects
   - Have a distinct JTBD, trajectory, and failure mode from other segments

3. Include a mandatory "Gaps vs. positioning" section for each segment.

Respond ONLY with YAML:

```yaml
segments:
  - name: "[behavioral descriptor — not demographic]"
    description: "[2-3 sentences on what defines this segment behaviorally]"
    subject_ids:
      - "subject-XX"
    primary_jtbd: "[what they are hiring a tool to do]"
    adoption_trajectory_shape: "[how they evaluate and decide]"
    dominant_constraint_profile: "[what limits their choices]"
    dominant_failure_mode: "[what causes rejection or abandonment]"
    gaps_vs_product_positioning: |
      [What this segment needs that the product currently does not offer or
       does not communicate. Be specific about the mismatch.]
```
